These questions are similar in that the interviewer is trying to get an idea of your general understanding of State and the tools available, as well as what not to do.

There are third party tools, like Redux, but, for a native approach, using the browsers's localStorage or session storage is one method. Browser cookies are available and used basically the same way. It is important to plan this out well. It is easy for this to become very complex and hard to maintain.

While global variables can work to maintain State, use of these is strongly discouraged. Global variables can become unreiable if new scripts or plugins use the same name for a global variable and overwrite our variable.

