214.answer:
These type of questions are generally designed to see if we have dealt with pass-by-reference vs pass-by-value issues. The interviewer will want to know if we understand why some processes work and some do not.

Options for created a deep copy.
1. Spread one object into a new object.
2. Stringify the object and the parse it into a new object.
3. Create a recursive function that copies each item.

const user = {
  firstName: 'Lando',
  middleName: 'Smoothie',
  lastName: 'Calrissian',
  nickName: 'Smuggler Extraordinaire '
};
const user2 = user;
const user4 = {
  ...user
};
const user3 = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(user));

Checking if one is a reference to another:
Simply trying to compare the two will not work as the values are not directly compared and the object itself is never going to match another. Recursivly comparing calues will only tell us if the values are teh same, not if one is a reference to the other. Object.is() can be used to tell if the one object is a reference to another.


console.log(Object.is(user, user4));  // false
console.log(Object.is(user, user3));  // false
console.log(Object.is(user, user2));  // true

