	p::first-letter {
		font-size: 50px;
	}

	p::first-line {
		color: orange;
		letter-spacing: 0.5em;
	}

	p::before {
		content: 'THIS IS BEFORE ---- ';
		color: darkblue;
		background-color: yellowgreen;
	}

	p::after {
		content: '--- THIS IS AFTER';
		background: gray;
		color: aquamarine;
	}


HTML
	<p>The first line will be orange and have letter-spacing applied. The first line changes as the element size changes. The resat of the line will be black, except for the ::before and ::after pseudo-elements. 
	</p>

