	Here are the basics to know:
	- z-index only works on positioned elements (position: absolute, position: relative, position: fixed, or position: sticky).

	- Elements usually stack with the items that are lower in the DOM appearing on top. z-index can change that for an element using a integer. The higher the number, the higher it goes on the element stack.

	- Understanding how the parent-child relationship works is very important for understanding how z-index will affect the elements. If element A has children, but element B sits on top of it, then no child element A can ever be higher than element B. No matter how high we make the z-index setting. 

